    }, {
      "columnQualifier" : "20250922",
      "minutesListened" : 0,
      "reason" : "MOST_DIVERSE_DAY",
      "title" : "The day you let 45 voices paint your morning in every shade",
      "description" : "Before sunrise, you stitched together filmi classics, lo-fi detours, and a dash of Marathi pop—Javed Bashir, Shreya Ghoshal, and Pritam all taking turns. By late morning, the queue had spanned six genres and a full 45 artists, with “Chup Chup Ke” and “Falak Tak” making their mark. 139 minutes, 29 tracks—your most diverse day of the year.",
      "filedUnderTags" : "[playlist mosaic, genre-spanning set]"
